                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17599744" author="hachikuji" created="Sat, 3 Sep 2022 00:27:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Worth mentioning that the alternative is to make the server more permissive and just ignore instance ID if it is set in OffsetCommit while memberId is empty.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17599901" author="dajac" created="Sat, 3 Sep 2022 11:36:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The advantage of being more permissive on the server side is that it would fix the issue for existing consumers. We should perhaps do both.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17600784" author="ijuma" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2022 14:06:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it&apos;s reasonably simple, it does make sense to do it on both sides since upgrades are done independently for clients and brokers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17600876" author="jagsancio" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2022 16:26:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hachikuji&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hachikuji&quot;&gt;hachikuji&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dajac&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dajac&quot;&gt;dajac&lt;/a&gt; Is this a blocker for 3.3.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
